### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

In the zoneless application, I've created an observable from the signal using `toObservable` method. When the signal value is updated then the observable doesn't emit updated values. Only the initial value was emitted.

I've created an example in Stackblitz. Note: it works perfectly fine with the zone.

Sample code snippets below:

Some state service with signals
```ts
@Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })
export class StateService {
  // I would like to keep _state as private, due to encapsulation
  private readonly _state = signal(false);

  // Expose state, similar like asObservable
  state = computed(this._state);

  toggle(): void {
    console.log(`State before change: ${this.state()}`);
    this._state.update((state) => !state); // I've tested also other methods like set, mutate
    console.log(`State after change: ${this.state()}`);
  }
}
```
The component which uses `toObservable`. 

```ts
@Component({
  selector: 'my-app',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [CommonModule],
  template: `
    <span>Current value: {{ state$ | async }}</span>
    <button (click)="changeState()">Change state</button>
  `,
})
export class App implements OnInit {
  name = 'Angular';

  private readonly stateService = inject(StateService);
  state$ = toObservable(this.stateService.state); // I've also tried to connect with private signal: _state

  ngOnInit(): void {
    // emits only the initial value in zoneless mode
    this.state$.subscribe((value) => {
      console.log(value);
    });
  }

  changeState(): void {
    this.stateService.toggle();
  }
}

bootstrapApplication(App, {
  providers: [{ provide: NgZone, useClass: ÉµNoopNgZone }], // uncomment to make app zoneless
  // providers: [], // uncomment to make app using zone
});

```

